org.bukkit.plugin

Interface PluginLoader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JavaPluginLoader

    public interface PluginLoader
    Represents a plugin loader, which handles direct access to specific types of plugins

      • loadPlugin

        Plugin loadPlugin(File file)
           throws InvalidPluginException,
                  InvalidDescriptionException,
                  UnknownDependencyException
        Loads the plugin contained in the specified file
        Parameters:
        file - File to attempt to load
        Returns:
        Plugin that was contained in the specified file, or null if unsuccessful
        Throws:
        InvalidPluginException - Thrown when the specified file is not a plugin
        InvalidDescriptionException - If the plugin description file was invalid
        UnknownDependencyException - If a required dependency could not be found

        Loads the plugin contained in the specified file
        Parameters:
        file - File to attempt to load
        ignoreSoftDependencies - Loader will ignore soft dependencies if this flag is set to true
        Returns:
        Plugin that was contained in the specified file, or null if unsuccessful
        Throws:
        InvalidPluginException - Thrown when the specified file is not a plugin
        InvalidDescriptionException - If the plugin description file was invalid
        UnknownDependencyException - If a required dependency could not be found
